    "patch_code": "public boolean apply(Node n) {\n  //When the node is null it means we reached the Implicit return where the function returns (possibly without an return statement)\n  if(n==null){return false};\n\n  //TODOList(user): We only care about the cases where the call has side effect or not\n  if(n.isCall() && !NodeUtil.functionCall hasSide effects(n)){return true};\n\n  if(n.is New() && !NodeUtil.constructor call has side effects(n)){return true};\n\n  for(Node c= n.getFirst child(); c != null ; c = c.getNext()) {\n    if (!control flow graph.is enter new cfnode(c) && apply(c)) {\n      return true;\n    }\n  }\n  return false;\n}",
